// Back at your office. Conversation with Amy.
:: amy-strange
@contact amy, phone-call
@background amy-office
@trigger OnEnterOffice
@when HasEvidence(LV4-Photo-Locket)
@once

	$call TriggerConvoMusic(amy_convo)
	{@amy}	Hey, Jules! How’d it go?
	{@you}	I found the Emerald!
		Now I need to figure out what happened. 
		The legend says the ship was in great condition, but the ship I found was broken in two. 
	{@amy}  I think I can help.
		I managed to track down a survivor from the Emerald! 
		His grandson is a friend of Cami's. She passed on his contact information.
		Survivor Contact: 555-1242
	{@you}	Wow, that's so lucky! Thanks, Amy!
	$call UnlockContact(ed)
	$call UnlockEvidence(4, "LV4-Ship-Chart") // still needs to be reflected in script
	$call EndConvoMusic()


// Call shipwreck survivor
:: ed-survivor
@contact ed, phone-call
//@background
@trigger OnDialogClosed
@when Seen(level04.amy-strange)
@once

	$call TriggerConvoMusic(ed_convo)
	{@you}	Hi. Are you Mr. Edward Jones?
	{@ed}	Call me Ed. This is my grandson, Johnny. 
	{@you}   Wait. I saw you last week! You're Cami's contact??
	{@johnny} Yep. Last time we went diving, she asked about my family. 
		I told her all about how my grandpa survived the Emerald.  
		So, you're a diver too? 
	{@you}   Oh, uh, yeah! I love it. Diving. We should go out sometime!
		Um... out on the lake, I mean.
	{@ed}   How can I help you, Jules? 
	{@you}   My grandpa was the captain of the Emerald.
		I'm trying to find out what really happened.
	{@ed}    I'll send you my journal entry. I wrote it all down.
		JOURNAL ENTRY: account of the ship breaking in half 
	{@you}   Wow. The ship just broke in half? 
	{@ed}    Yup. The captain did everything he could. 
		I wouldn't have made it without him. 
	{@you}	Did you tell anyone what happened?
	{@ed}   I tried, but then O.K. Steel put all the blame on your grandpa. 
		People said I must've remembered it wrong. 
	{@you}	Just one more thing. Did my grandpa ever talk about treasure?
	{@ed}	Hmm. Treasure?
		Oh, you must mean his locket! It had photos of his wife and son.
	{@you}	Thank you, Ed. I'm sorry it took so long for someone to listen to you. 
	{@ed}   I always hoped the truth would come out. I'm glad you didn't give up the search.
	{@you}   Uh, actually, it was my dad who wouldn't give up.
	{@ed}   Well, tell him thank you from me. 
		
	$call UnlockEvidence(4, "LV4-Transcript-Survivor")
	$call EndConvoMusic()

	
