// Conversation with Reya--same as the beginning convo screen
:: reya-end
@contact reya, phone-call
//@background
@trigger OnBoardComplete
@once

	$call TriggerConvoMusic(reya_convo)
	{@reya}  Well??? What happened?
		It was the Emerald, right? Wasn't it? 
	{@you}   Yep.
	{@reya}  YESS!!!!
	{@dad}   I can't believe it. After all this time.
	{@you}   The wreck wasn't Grandpa's fault. You were right, Dad.
	{@reya}   Whoa. Seriously?? I thought Grandpa was this wild, daredevil type guy. Always going on adventures. 
	{@you}   You can be adventurous and follow the rules at the same time, Reya. Like Grandpa.
	{@reya}   Hmm. I guess so...
	{@dad}   Fill us in, Jules. What really happened?
	{@you}   The Emerald was sent on an unplanned run. The waves were rough, but the ship was sailing smoothly.
		Then there was a loud BANG, and the ship suddenly broke in half!
		Grandpa helped launch a life raft, but he wasn't able to make it to safety. 
	{@reya}  I don't get it. How could a huge freighter just break apart?
	{@you}   Mom found out that weak steel was used in its construction.
	{@dad}   That's awful. I need to get the word out!
		What if there are more disasters that could be prevented?
	{@reya}  Yeah, yeah. That's important and all, but what about the treasure? 
	{@you}	The treasure was Grandpa’s locket.
	{@reya}  What?? That's it? 
		Well, at least you can get a permit and go grab the locket. I know you're jealous of mine.
	{@you}   Actually, I think I'll donate it to the museum.
		 I want everyone to be able to see it and remember what happened.
	{@reya}  Ugh. Boring, but whatever.
		 Oh, by the way, my friend Johnny said he met you.
	{@you}   What?? You know him, too?
	{@reya}  He wants to hang out with us, but I told him you're too busy with paperwork.
	$call TriggerCutscene()
	$call EndConvoMusic()